  "name": "Nagaraja COU1 — Total knee arthroplasty tibial tray micromotion credibility assessment",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for finite-element prediction of tibial tray micromotion in cementless total knee arthroplasty (TKA) under physiological gait loading. COU1 evaluates whether the FE model can predict relative micromotion at the implant-bone interface to support primary stability claims for a Class II orthopedic device at Model Risk Level 3. All 13 credibility factors are assessed; achieved levels meet or exceed required levels at MRL 3. Monte Carlo sensitivity analysis on bone material properties and press-fit interference was performed. Decision: Accepted.",
