        "type": "AcceptanceCriteria",
        "name": "Model form — linear elastic bone with nonlinear frictional contact",
        "description": "Model form assumptions (linear elastic bone, rigid implant, Coulomb friction contact) must be justified relative to the micromotion QoI and loading regime. Justification must reference published literature supporting the assumptions within the COU operating envelope."
      },
      "rationale": "Linear elastic bone is appropriate for the sub-yield strain regime under normal gait loading (peak strains < 2000 µε). Rigid implant assumption is justified by the 100-fold stiffness ratio between CoCr alloy and cortical bone. Coulomb friction (µ=0.6) is consistent with published porous titanium–bone interface measurements. Model form is well-supported for this COU."
